The Vice President, along with his family, visited Yellowstone National Park and expressed his commitment to conserving and preserving national parks. He commended the men and women who work in the National Park Service and discussed the backlog in maintenance funding. The administration has proposed a new fund that would invest 50% of revenues from leases on public lands back into national parks. The Vice President expressed hope for bipartisan support and clearing the maintenance backlog. When asked about the President's 2020 budget, the Vice President stated that they believe the funding level is appropriate and that the new fund will meet the maintenance obligations of national parks. He also mentioned the importance of state-controlled parks and working with states to preserve national parks. The Vice President and the Secretary of the Interior confirmed that the proposed funding stream would include national monuments, preserves, and Indian schools.